{
  "text": "In recent years, Printed Circuit Board (PCB) contains more conduct paths to provide functional variety but in a much smaller layout area [CITATION_1] . One advanced type of PCB called the Ball Grid Array (BGA) substrate (see Fig. 1 ), has been extensively used to connect the solder ball array on Integrated Circuits (ICs) for electrical conductivity in Surface Mount Technology (SMT) [CITATION_2] . Because the linewidths and the linespacings on BGA substrates are more sophisticated than conventional PCBs, defects are hard to detect and they could seriously disable conductivity.",
  "citation_candidates": [
